<eesti> (90/554/EM&Uuml;) </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular the first subparagraph of Article 93 (2) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 93 l&otilde;ike 2 esimest l&otilde;iku, </eesti>
<inglise> Having given formal notice to the parties concerned to submit their comments, in accordance with the first subparagraph of Article 93 (2) of the Treaty, </inglise>
<eesti> olles ametlikult teatanud asjaomastele pooltele, et nad esitaksid oma selgitused koosk&otilde;las asutamislepingu artikli 93 l&otilde;ike 2 esimese l&otilde;iguga, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in the light of the following: </inglise>
<eesti> ning pidades silmas j&auml;rgmist: </eesti>
<inglise> I. Background and description - Procedure </inglise>
<eesti> I. Asjaolud - Menetlus </eesti>
<inglise> By letters from its Permanent Representation to the European Communities dated 29 September 1988 and 30 January 1989, recorded as received by the Commission on 4 October 1988 and 1 February 1989 respectively, the Spanish Government notified the Commission, pursuant to Article 93 (3) of the EEC Treaty, of a draft ministerial order on logistic support for the fishing fleet in 1988 and supplied additional information requested by the Commission on 25 October 1988. </inglise>
<eesti> Oma alalise esinduse Euroopa &uuml;hendustes kirjadega 29. septembrist 1988 ja 30. jaanuarist 1989, mille komisjon registreeris vastavalt 4. oktoobril 1988 ja 1. veebruaril 1989, teatas Hispaania valitsus komisjonile EM&Uuml; asutamislepingu artikli 93 l&otilde;ike 3 kohaselt Hispaania ministri m&auml;&auml;ruse eeln&otilde;ust, mis k&auml;sitleb kalalaevastikule 1988. aastal antavat logistilist abi, ning esitas t&auml;iendavad andmed, mida komisjon oli 25. oktoobril 1988 n&otilde;udnud. </eesti>
<inglise> Aid for logistic support for the fishing fleet </inglise>
<eesti> Abi kalalaevastikule antava logistilise abi jaoks </eesti>
<inglise> To facilitate supplies to the Spanish fishing fleets operating in distant areas and hence experiencing supply difficulties, the Spanish Government had allocated a budget of about ECU 750 000 for assisting supply operations for fishing vessels by means of logistic support vessels (supplying victuals, fuel, etc.). </inglise>
<eesti> Et parandada Hispaania kalalaevade varustamist, kes t&ouml;&ouml;tavad kaugetes piirkondades ja kelle varustamine on seet&otilde;ttu raskeks osutunud, on Hispaania valitsus eraldanud eelarvelistest vahenditest umbes 750 000 ek&uuml;&uuml;d kalalaevade varustamistoimingute toetamiseks logistilise abi laevade abil (kes varustavad laevu pardavarude, k&uuml;tte jms). </eesti>
<inglise> The draft order lays down the procedure for processing such aid. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse eeln&otilde;us n&auml;hakse ette niisuguse abi andmise kord. </eesti>
<inglise> The aid, intended to cover up to 75 % of the costs of logistic support vessels, was to be granted by way of priority to supply operations for fishing vessels which operated permanently in fishing zones where they could not obtain supplies at Community ports and which, by reason of the difficulties they experienced in obtaining supplies at foreign ports, were obliged to resort to logistic support vessels. </inglise>
<eesti> Abi, mis on ette n&auml;htud logistilise abi laevade kulude katmiseks 75% ulatuses, antakse eelk&otilde;ige nende kalalaevade varustamiseks, mis tegutsevad pidevalt kalastusv&ouml;&ouml;ndites, kus nad ei saa hankida varusid &uuml;henduse sadamates ning on sunnitud kasutama logistilise abi laevu raskuste t&otilde;ttu, mida nad on kogenud varude hankimisel v&auml;lissadamates. </eesti>
<inglise> Owners of fishing vessels belonging to a producers' organization recognized by Spain for deep-sea fishing would be able to submit applications for the aid in question accompanied by documentary evidence of the supply operation involving a logistic support vessel. </inglise>
<eesti> Hispaania poolt tunnustatud avamerep&uuml;&uuml;giga tegelevatesse tootjaorganisatsioonidesse kuuluvate kalalaevade omanikud v&otilde;ivad esitada k&otilde;nealuse abi taotlusi, millele lisatakse dokumentaalsed t&otilde;endid varustustoimingute kohta logistilise abi laeva abil. </eesti>
<inglise> Applications which were approved would be eligible for partial reimbursement by the Spanish authorities of the cost of the logistic support vessel used. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui taotlus rahuldatakse, h&uuml;vitavad Hispaania ametiasutused osaliselt logistilise abi laevade prahikulud. </eesti>
<inglise> The aid provided for in the abovementioned aid scheme would apply primarily to fleets of seiners and freezer-trawlers (tuna boats and cod, mollusc and crustacean fishing units). </inglise>
<eesti> Eespool nimetatud toetuskava alusel antavat abi kohaldatakse eelk&otilde;ige seinerite ja k&uuml;lmutustraalerite suhtes (tuuni- ja tursap&uuml;&uuml;gilaevad ning molluski- ja v&auml;hip&uuml;&uuml;gilaevad). </eesti>
<inglise> The draft concerns supplies to fishing vessels using logistic supply vessels in ordinary circumstances, it does not refer to emergencies. </inglise>
<eesti> Eeln&otilde;u k&auml;sitleb kalalaevade varustamist, kes kasutavad logistilise abi laevu tavalistes tingimustes, mitte eriolukorras. </eesti>
<inglise> Examination by the Commission </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjonipoolne kontroll </eesti>
<inglise> After its first examination, the Commission took the view that the aid for logistic support for the fishing fleet constituted an operating aid not requiring the beneficiaries to provide anything in return, the result of which would be to reduce production costs. </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;rast esimest kontrolli oli komisjon seisukohal, et abiks kalalaevastikule antavaks logistiliseks abiks koosnes tegevusabist, mille puhul abisaajatelt ei n&otilde;uta vastutasuks midagi, mille tulemuseks oleks tootmiskulude v&auml;henemine. </eesti>
<inglise> Such aid had a marked direct effect on competition and trade between Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Niisugusel abil on m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rselt otsene m&otilde;ju liikmesriikidevahelisele konkurentsile ja kaubavahetusele. </eesti>
<inglise> It was thus considered incompatible with the common market under Article 92 of the EEC Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> Seega loeti abi EM&Uuml; asutamislepingu artikli 92 kohaselt &uuml;histuruga kokkusobimatuks. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission therefore decided to initiate the procedure laid down in Article 93 (3) of the Treaty in respect of the aid in question and, by letter of 31 March 1989, gave notice to the Spanish Government to submit its comments. </inglise>
<eesti> Seet&otilde;ttu otsustas komisjon alustada k&otilde;nealuse abi suhtes asutamislepingu artikli 93 l&otilde;ikes 3 etten&auml;htud menetlust ja teatas oma 31. m&auml;rtsi 1989. aasta kirjas Hispaania valitsusele, et viimane esitaks oma selgitused. </eesti>
<inglise> Comments of interested parties </inglise>
<eesti> Huvitatud poolte selgitused </eesti>
<inglise> Only one Spanish producers' organization submitted its comments to the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> Ainult &uuml;ks Hispaania tootjaorganisatsioon esitas komisjonile oma selgitused. </eesti>
<inglise> It regretted the delay between the first notification and the Commission's decision to initiate the procedure laid down in Article 92 (2) of the Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> Ta avaldas kahetsust viivituse p&auml;rast esimese teate ja komisjoni otsuse vahel alustada asutamislepingu artikli 92 l&otilde;ikes 2 etten&auml;htud menetlust. </eesti>
<inglise> Stressing that it was exceptional for logistic support vessels to be used to supply fishing vessels and that this happened only where distant ports did not provide supply facilities or did so at exorbitant prices, it took the view that the draft aid notified constituted an aid to technical assistance at sea as referred to in point II.B.5 of the guidelines for the examination of state aid in the fisheries sector (1). </inglise>
<eesti> R&otilde;hutades, et kalalaevade varustamine logistilise abi laevadega oli erandlik ja et toimub ainult siis, kui varude t&auml;iendamine kaugetes sadamates ei olnud v&otilde;imalik v&otilde;i oli v&otilde;imalik &uuml;ksnes p&ouml;&ouml;rase r&ouml;&ouml;velliku hinna eest, oli ta seisukohal, et teatavaks tehtud abi eeln&otilde;u v&otilde;ib vaadelda tehnilise abina merel, nagu on m&auml;rgitud kalandussektoris riigiabi kontrollimise suuniste punktis II.B.5. (1) </eesti>
<inglise> II. </inglise>
<eesti> II. </eesti>
<inglise> Comments by the Spanish Government </inglise>
<eesti> Hispaania valitsuse selgitused </eesti>
<inglise> By letter of 10 May 1989, in reply to the Commission's letter of 31 March 1989 giving notice to the Spanish Government to submit its comments, the Spanish Government submitted several comments on the principle and advisability of the aid scheme. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastuseks komisjoni 31. m&auml;rtsi 1989. aasta kirjale, kus teatati Hispaania valitsusele, et ta peab esitama oma selgitused, esitas Hispaania valitsuse oma 10. mai 1989 kirjas selgitused abikava olemuse ja kohasuse kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> The Spanish Government took the view that this was aid for supplying fishing vessels and confined to immediate needs which the fishing vessels could not normally meet by their own means as regards equipment and supplies. </inglise>
<eesti> Hispaania valitsus oli seisukohal, et see oli abi kalalaevade varustamiseks ja piirdus otseste vajadustega, mida kalalaevad oma seadmete ja varude abil ei saanud normaalselt rahuldada. </eesti>
<inglise> Such aid did not distort or threaten to distort competition between Member States and in any case did not adversely affect trading conditions to an extent contrary to the common interest. </inglise>
<eesti> Niisugune abi ei moonutanud ega &auml;hvardanud moonutada liikmesriikidevahelist konkurentsi ning mitte mingil juhul ei avaldanud negatiivset m&otilde;ju kaubavahetuse tingimustele m&auml;&auml;ral, mis oleks vastuolus &uuml;histe huvidega. </eesti>
<inglise> The aid in question could therefore be regarded as aid to technical assistance at sea as provided for in point II.B.5 of the abovementioned guidelines. In this respect there was a linguistic inconsistency between the Commission's letter of 31 March 1989 and the Spanish and French texts of the guidelines concerning the words'aux cas d'urgence' ('in emergencies'), which were translated in the Spanish version of the guidelines by'a la necesidades imediatas' and in the letter by'situacion de emergencia'. </inglise>
<eesti> Seet&otilde;ttu v&otilde;ib k&otilde;nealust abi vaadelda abina tehnilise abi jaoks merel, mis on s&auml;testatud eespool nimetatud suuniste punktis II.B.5. Selles suhtes oli komisjoni 31. m&auml;rtsi 1989. aasta kirja ning hispaania- ja prantsuskeelsete suuniste vahel keeleline vastuolu s&otilde;nade "aux cas d'urgence" ("eriolukorras") puhul, mis oli hispaaniakeelsetes suunistes t&otilde;lgitud "a la necesidades imediatas" ja kirjas "situaci&oacute;n de emergencia". </eesti>
<inglise> As for the advisability of granting the aid in question, the Spanish Government indicated the following reasons: </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealuse abi andmise kohasust p&otilde;hjendas Hispaania valitsus j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise> - The long-distance fleet was at a disadvantage compared with owners obtaining supplies at Community ports as regards the distance from supply ports and the prices charged at those ports. </inglise>
<eesti> - Kaugs&otilde;idulaevastik on halvemas olukorras v&otilde;rreldes nende omanikega, kes hangivad varud &uuml;henduse sadamatest, arvestades kaugust sadamast, kus varusid hangitakse, ja nendes sadamates n&otilde;utavaid hindu. </eesti>
<inglise> - The long-distance fleet was at a relative competitive disadvantage on the Community market compared with the Community inshore and high-sea fishing fleets (fresh substitute products), compared with the fleets operating near the usual fishing zones, which benefited from preference at the Community frontier and compared with the fleets of the State-trading countries, which were heavily subsidized and which carried on their activities benefiting from the same conditions of access to the traditional fishing zones. </inglise>
<eesti> - Kaugs&otilde;idulaevastik on suhteliselt ebasoodsas olukorras v&otilde;rreldes &uuml;henduse rannas&otilde;idu ja avamere kalalaevastikega (v&auml;rsked asendustooted), v&otilde;rreldes tavap&auml;rastes kalastusv&ouml;&ouml;ndite l&auml;hedal tegutsevate laevastikega, mis saavad oma tooteid soodsamalt &uuml;hendusse importida, ja v&otilde;rreldes riikliku kaubandusega maade laevastikega, mis saavad riigilt suurt toetust ja mis tegutsevad, kasutades samu juurdep&auml;&auml;sutingimusi traditsioonilistele kalastusv&ouml;&ouml;nditele. </eesti>
<inglise> III. </inglise>
<eesti> III. </eesti>
<inglise> Legal assessment </inglise>
<eesti> &Otilde;iguslik hinnang </eesti>
<inglise> The reimbursement of part of the cost of the support vessel used to supply a fishing vessel as provided for in the draft order notified may be granted to owners who are members of a producers' organization recognized for deep-sea fishing. </inglise>
<eesti> Kalalaeva varustamiseks kasutatava abilaeva kulusid v&otilde;ib teatavaks tehtud m&auml;&auml;ruse eeln&otilde;u kohaselt osaliselt h&uuml;vitada omanikele, kes on s&uuml;vamerep&uuml;&uuml;giga tegeleva tunnustatud tootjaorganisatsiooni liikmed. </eesti>
<inglise> In accordance with Article 1 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 105/76 of 19 January 1976 on the recognition of producers' organizations in the fishing industry (2), the Member State is responsible for the recognition of the producers' organizations referred to in Article 5 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 3796/81 of 29 December 1981 on the common organization of the market in fishery products (3). </inglise>
<eesti> Koosk&otilde;las n&otilde;ukogu 19. jaanuari 1976. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 105/76 kalandussektori tootjaorganisatsioonide tunnustamise kohta (2) artikliga 1 vastutab n&otilde;ukogu 29. detsembri 1981. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3796/81 kalap&uuml;&uuml;gitooteturu &uuml;hise korraldamise kohta (3) artiklis 5 nimetatud tootjaorganisatsioonide tunnustamise eest liikmesriik. </eesti>
<inglise> In principle this reimbursement is confined to owners involved in deep-sea fishing using a logistic support vessel to supply their fishing vessel. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;ldjuhul piirdub see kulude h&uuml;vitamine omanikega, kes tegelevad avamerep&uuml;&uuml;giga ja kasutavad oma kalalaeva varustamiseks logistilise abi laeva. </eesti>
<inglise> Preference will be given to applications relating to supply operations for vessels which operate permanently in fishing zones with no possibility of obtaining supplies at Community ports and which, by reason of the difficulties they experience in obtaining supplies at foreign ports, are obliged to resort to logistic support vessels. </inglise>
<eesti> Eelistatakse taotlusi, mis on seotud nende laevade varustamisega, kes tegutsevad alaliselt kalastusv&ouml;&ouml;ndites, kus ei ole v&otilde;imalik hankida varusid &uuml;henduse sadamatest, ja varustamisraskuste t&otilde;ttu v&auml;lissadamates on nad kohustatud kasutama logistilise abi laevu. </eesti>
<inglise> These are supply operations inherent in the fishing activity of the vessel in question which do not solely concern emergencies or unforeseen situations. </inglise>
<eesti> Need varustamistoimingud on laeva kalap&uuml;&uuml;gitegevuse loomulik osa ega kujuta endast eriolukorda v&otilde;i etten&auml;gematut olukorda. </eesti>
<inglise> The logistic operations play an important role in general, in particular in the operation of vessels engaged in deep-sea fishing. </inglise>
<eesti> Logistiline tegevus on &uuml;ldse t&auml;htis tegevus, eriti avamerep&uuml;&uuml;giga tegelevate laevade puhul. </eesti>
<inglise> Owners of such vessels have to seek a balance between, on the one hand, maximizing the number of fishing days for the sake of the return on the fishing activity of the vessel and, on the other hand, minimizing the number of days when the vessel is unable to engage in fishing because it must attend to needs such as supplies, replacement of the crew, transport of catches and maintenance of the vessel and fishing gear; in this connection they have to choose between the facilities offered by the coastal states and using a support vessel. </inglise>
<eesti> Niisuguste laevade omanikud peavad saavutama tasakaalu &uuml;helt poolt kalap&uuml;&uuml;gip&auml;evade arvu suurendamise (et laeva kalap&uuml;&uuml;gitegevus tooks tulu) ja teiselt poolt nende p&auml;evade arvu v&auml;hendamise vahel, kui laev ei saa tegelda kalap&uuml;&uuml;giga varustamise, meeskonna vahetuse, saagi transportimise ning laeva ja p&uuml;&uuml;givahendite hoolduse t&otilde;ttu; Seoses sellega peavad nad valima, kas kasutada rannikuriikide pakutud v&otilde;imalusi v&otilde;i abilaevu. </eesti>
<inglise> Under these circumstances reimbursement of part of the cost of the support vessel used to supply his fishing boat is therefore likely to reduce the production costs and boost the income of the beneficiary of this reimbursement. </inglise>
<eesti> Nende asjaolude t&otilde;ttu v&auml;hendab tema kalalaeva varustamiseks kasutatud abilaeva kulude osaline h&uuml;vitamine t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt tema tootmiskulusid ja suurendab selle h&uuml;vitise saaja tulusid. </eesti>
<inglise> The objective of the draft order is to enable the deep-sea fishing fleet to benefit from supply costs similar to those prevailing in Community ports. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse eeln&otilde;u eesm&auml;rk on v&otilde;imaldada avamerep&uuml;&uuml;gi kalalaevastikul kanda sama suuri varustamiskulusid kui &uuml;henduse sadamas valitsevad kulud. </eesti>
<inglise> In view of this objective and the rules of application laid down in the draft order notified, the Commission takes the view that reimbursement of part of the cost of the support vessel used for supplying the fishing vessel constitutes an operating aid without any real reciprocity on the part of the beneficiary. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda eesm&auml;rki ja teatavaks tehtud m&auml;&auml;ruse eeln&otilde;us s&auml;testatud rakenduseeskirju silmas pidades on komisjon seisukohal, et kalalaeva varustamiseks kasutatava abilaeva kulude osaline h&uuml;vitamine on tegevusabi, kus abisaaja ei pea tegelikult vastutasuks midagi tegema. </eesti>
<inglise> This aid, applying to the Spanish deep-sea fishing fleet, which consists of seiners and freezer-trawlers (tuna boats and cod, mollusc and crustacean fishing units) is likely to strengthen the competitive position of eligible Spanish shipowners vis-&igrave;-vis owners of fishing vessels in other Member States, e.g. Italy and France, engaged in deep-sea fishing. </inglise>
<eesti> See abi, mida kohaldatakse Hispaania avamerep&uuml;&uuml;gi kalalaevastiku suhtes, mis koosneb seineritest ja k&uuml;lmutustraaleritest (tuuni- ja tursap&uuml;&uuml;gilaevad ning molluski- ja v&auml;hip&uuml;&uuml;gilaevad), tugevdab t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt abik&otilde;lblike Hispaania laevaomanike konkurentsiv&otilde;imet muude liikmesriikide, n&auml;it Itaalia ja Prantsusmaa kalalaevaomanike suhtes, kes tegelevad avamere kalap&uuml;&uuml;giga. </eesti>
<inglise> The Spanish fleet is the largest deep-sea fishing fleet (in terms of production and the number of vessels) of this type in the Community with a production figure for 1988 of about 185 000 tonnes of frozen tuna, 60 000 tonnes of molluscs and crustaceans and 120 000 tonnes of frozen cod. </inglise>
<eesti> Hispaania laevastik on &uuml;henduse seda t&uuml;&uuml;pi suurim avamerep&uuml;&uuml;gi kalalaevastik (toodangu ja laevade arvu poolest), kelle toodang 1988. aastal oli umbes 185 000 tonni k&uuml;lmutatud tuunikala, 60 000 tonni molluskeid ja koorikloomi ja 120 000 tonni k&uuml;lmutatud turska. </eesti>
<inglise> Out of the total landings of these products by the Community fishing fleet, the Spanish fleet accounts for over 60 % and for some of these products, such as frozen cod, the percentage is as much as 80 %. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;henduse kalalaevastiku nende toodete lossitud kogusaagist on Hispaania laevastiku osa &uuml;le 60% ning k&uuml;lmutatud tursa puhul koguni 80%. </eesti>
<inglise> The aid does therefore distort competition in the fishing sector. </inglise>
<eesti> Seet&otilde;ttu moonutab nimetatud abi konkurentsi kalandussektoris. </eesti>
<inglise> Intra-Community trade in the products in question is substantial. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendusesisene k&otilde;nealuste toodete kaubandus on t&auml;htis. </eesti>
<inglise> Spanish imports from and exports to other Member States in 1988 totalled 9 800 tonnes and 54 000 tonnes of tuna respectively, 154 000 and 48 000 tonnes of molluscs and crustaceans and 74 000 and 19 700 tonnes of cod. </inglise>
<eesti> Hispaania import muudest liikmesriikidest ja eksport muudesse liikmesriikidesse oli 1988. aastal kokku vastavalt 9800 tonni ja 54 000 tonni tuunikala, 154 000 ja 48 000 tonni molluskeid ja koorikloomi ja 74 000 ja 19 700 tonni turska. </eesti>
<inglise> The aid does therefore affect trade between Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Seet&otilde;ttu m&otilde;jutab nimetatud abi liikmesriikidevahelist kaubavahetust. </eesti>
<inglise> Under these circumstances, these aids, by affecting trade between Member States, distort or threaten to distort competition, particularly vis-&igrave;-vis shipowners in other Member States engaged in deep-sea fishing who face a similar situation to Spanish shipowners. </inglise>
<eesti> Nendel asjaoludel moonutab nimetatud abi liikmesriikidevahelise kaubavahetuse m&otilde;jutamisega konkurentsi v&otilde;i &auml;hvardab seda moonutada eelk&otilde;ige muude liikmesriikide laevaomanike suhtes, kes tegelevad avamerep&uuml;&uuml;giga, kes on Hispaania laevaomanikega v&otilde;rreldes samas olukorras. </eesti>
<inglise> The aid cannot be regarded as compatible with the common market on the grounds of the disadvantages cited by the Spanish Government or the translation of certain words referring to a category of aid which definitely does not cover the aid in question. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda abi ei saa lugeda &uuml;histuruga kokkusobivaks Hispaania valitsuse poolt tsiteeritud ebasoodsate olukordade alusel v&otilde;i teatavate s&otilde;nade t&otilde;lke alusel, mis k&auml;sitlevad abi, mis kindlasti ei h&otilde;lma k&otilde;nesolevat abi. </eesti>
<inglise> IV. </inglise>
<eesti> IV. </eesti>
<inglise> The aid provided for in the draft order notified constitutes support measures financed by State resources and strengthening the competitive position of certain Spanish shipowners compared with those in other Member States and as such is subject to Article 92 (1) of the Treaty, which sets out the principle of incompatibility of such aid with the common market. </inglise>
<eesti> Teatavaks tehtud m&auml;&auml;ruse eeln&otilde;us s&auml;testatud abi koosneb toetusmeetmetest, mida rahastatakse riigi ressurssidest ja mis tugevdavad teatavate Hispaania laevaomanike konkurentsiv&otilde;imet v&otilde;rreldes muude liikmesriikide laevaomanikega ning mida tuleb seet&otilde;ttu anda koosk&otilde;las asutamislepingu artikli 92 l&otilde;ikega 1, milles on s&auml;testatud niisuguse abi &uuml;histuruga kokkusobimatuse p&otilde;him&otilde;te. </eesti>
<inglise> The exceptions to this principle listed in Article 92 (2) of the EEC Treaty do not apply in this case in view of the nature and the objectives of the aid envisaged, nor are they invoked by the Spanish Government. </inglise>
<eesti> Selle asutamislepingu artikli 92 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud p&otilde;him&otilde;tte erandeid k&auml;esoleval juhul ei kohaldata kavandatud abi laadi ja eesm&auml;rkide t&otilde;ttu ning ka Hispaania valitsus ei v&otilde;i neile tugineda. </eesti>
<inglise> The exceptions provided for in Article 92 (3) of the Treaty refer to objectives pursued in the interest of the Community not just that of particular sectors of a national economy. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutamislepingu artikli 92 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud erandid osutavad eesm&auml;rkidele, mida taotletakse kogu &uuml;henduse huvides, mitte aga teatavate rahvamajandussektorite huvides. </eesti>
<inglise> These exceptions must be strictly interpreted when any regional or sectoral aid scheme is considered. </inglise>
<eesti> Neid erandeid tuleb rangelt t&otilde;lgendada, kui k&otilde;ne all on &uuml;ksk&otilde;ik milline piirkondliku abi v&otilde;i konkreetsele sektorile antava abi kava. </eesti>
<inglise> They can be granted only in cases in which the Commission can establish that the aid is necessary to achieve the objectives specified in those provisions. </inglise>
<eesti> Erandeid v&otilde;ib lubada ainult juhtudel, mille puhul komisjon saab kindlaks teha, et abi on vajalik nende s&auml;tetega etten&auml;htud eesm&auml;rkide saavutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> Granting the said exemptions to aid without reciprocity would be tantamount to allowing damage to trade between Member States and distortions of competition unjustified in the Community interest. </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud erandite lubamine abi andmisel ilma vastutasuta oleks sama, mis lubada liikmesriikidevahelise kaubavahetuse kahjustamist ja konkurentsi moonutamist, mis oleks &uuml;henduse huvidest l&auml;htudes p&otilde;hjendamatu. </eesti>
<inglise> Reciprocity has been found to be lacking in the case in point and the Spanish Government has not been able to give, nor the Commission to find, a justification other than granting a financial advantage to the entire deep-sea fishing fleet encountering supply difficulties. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealusel juhul on leitud, et vastutasu puudub ja Hispaania valitsus ei ole suutnud esitada ega komisjon leida muud p&otilde;hjendust, kui finantssoodustuste andmine kogu avamerep&uuml;&uuml;gi kalalaevastikule, kellel on varustusraskusi. </eesti>
<inglise> This does not qualify the aid in question for one of the exceptions provided for in Article 92 (3) of the Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> See ei anna alust kohaldada k&otilde;nealuse abi suhtes asutamislepingu artikli 92 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud erandeid. </eesti>
<inglise> As regards the derogation for aid to promote the development of certain economic activities, the aid provided for in the draft in question is not likely to have the effect of economic development within the meaning of Article 92 (3) (c) of the Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> Mis puutub eranditesse abi andmisel teatava majandustegevuse arendamise edendamiseks, siis k&otilde;nealuses eeln&otilde;us etten&auml;htud abi t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt ei m&otilde;juta majandusarengut asutamislepingu artikli 92 l&otilde;ike 3 punkti c t&auml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise> Furthermore, the volume of intra-Community trade in fishery products precludes the view that trading conditions would not be affected to an extent contrary to the common interest. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendusesisese kalatoodete kaubavahetuse maht v&auml;listab seisukoha, et kaubandustingimusi ei m&otilde;jutata m&auml;&auml;ral, mis on vastuolus &uuml;henduse huvidega. </eesti>
<inglise> This is not operating aid directly connected with a restructuring plan deemed compatible with the common market. </inglise>
<eesti> See ei ole tegevusabi, mis on otseselt seotud &uuml;mberkorralduskavaga, mida loetakse &uuml;histuruga kokkusobivaks. </eesti>
<inglise> The general character of the aid precludes; from being regarded as aid to technical assistance at sea, compatible with the common market in so far as such assistance is provided only in emergencies which cannot be coped with by means of the equipment and supplies normally found on fishing vessels as referred to in point II.B.5 of the guidelines. The abovementioned point in the guidelines covering aid to fishing at sea actually concerns technical assistance at sea in really exceptional circumstances. </inglise>
<eesti> Abi &uuml;ldine laad v&auml;listab selle, et seda peetakse tehniliseks abiks merel, mis sobib kokku &uuml;histuruga niiv&otilde;rd, kuiv&otilde;rd niisugust abi antakse ainult eriolukorras, mida ei saa teha seadmete ja varustusega, mis on tavaliselt kalalaevadel olemas, nagu on osutatud suuniste punktis II.B.5. Eespool nimetatud suuniste punkt, mis reguleerib kalastusabi merel, k&auml;ib merel antava tehnilise abi kohta t&otilde;eliselt erandlikes olukordades. </eesti>
<inglise> In the light of the foregoing, the aid provided for in the draft order does not satisfy the conditions qualifying it for exceptions under Article 92 (2) and (3) and it is therefore incompatible with the common market, </inglise>
<eesti> Seoses eespool &ouml;elduga ei vasta m&auml;&auml;ruse eeln&otilde;us etten&auml;htud abi tingimustele, mille puhul kohaldatakse artikli 92 l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 etten&auml;htud erandeid ning on seet&otilde;ttu &uuml;histuruga kokkusobimatu, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DECISION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA OTSUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The aid for supply operations for fishing vessels engaged in deep-sea fishing involving logistic support vessels provided for in the Spanish draft ministerial order on logistic support for the fishing fleet in 1988, notified on 29 September 1988, is incompatible with the common market under Article 92 of the Treaty in so far as it is not granted for the purpose of technical assistance at sea only in emergencies which cannot be coped with by means of the equipment and supplies normally found on fishing vessels as provided for in the guidelines on State aids in the fisheries sector. </inglise>
<eesti> Abi kalalaevade varustamiseks, kes tegelevad avamerep&uuml;&uuml;giga, millesse on kaasatud logistilise abi laevad, mis on ette n&auml;htud Hispaania ministri m&auml;&auml;ruse eeln&otilde;us kalalaevastiku logistilise abi kohta 1988. aastal, millest teatati 29. septembril 1988, on &uuml;histuruga kokkusobimatu asutamislepingu artikli 92 kohaselt, sest seda ei anta tehnilise abina merel ainult eriolukorras, mida ei saa teha seadmete ja varustusega, mis on tavaliselt kalalaevadel olemas, nagu on ette n&auml;htud kalandussektori riigiabi suunistes. </eesti>
<inglise> The aid in question shall not be put into effect and shall not be granted. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealust abi ei tohi kehtestada ja seda saa anda. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Spain shall inform the Commission within two months from the notification of this Decision of the measures taken to comply with this Decision. </inglise>
<eesti> Hispaania informeerib komisjoni kahe kuu jooksul alates k&auml;esoleva otsuse teatavakstegemisest alates k&auml;esoleva otsuse t&auml;itmiseks v&otilde;etud meetmetest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision is addressed to the Kingdom of Spain. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus on adresseeritud Hispaania Kuningriigile. Br&uuml;ssel, 14. veebruar 1990 </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 14 February 1990. </inglise>
